Chelsea Vice-chairman Dies in Air Crash 
Matthew Harding, vice-chairman of English premier league soccer club
Chelsea, was killed in a helicopter crash on Tuesday night, according
to local TV channel on Wednesday.
The Sky television channel reported that Harding and four other people
were killed when their helicopter crashed with no survivors in
Cheshire, northern England, on the way back from Chelsea's League Cup
match in Bolton.
Harding, one of the wealthiest men in Britain, bought the club's
Stamford Bridge ground in 1995 for 26 million dollars and provided
further cash for stadium improvements and new players.
